<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1249] Rework Oracle LOB support</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1249</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We could probably get rid of the following Oracle-specific behaviour and code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;using non-embedded LOB handling when size of the value exceeds 4000 bytes/chars,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;using empty LOB when persisting a null value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Chances are the above behaviour is not needed starting from Oracle 9 or 10.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
